		Eat like a local: Dine at neighborhood tapas bars, street food vendors, and local markets instead of tourist-focused restaurants.
		Use public transportation: Barcelona has an efficient and affordable public transportation system, so skip the taxis and use the metro, buses, or bikes.
		Take advantage of free attractions: Many of Barcelona's famous landmarks and museums offer free admission on certain days or times.</turn>
		<turn type="student">In which year should I travel to see the Sagrada Familia finished?</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="Pi.ai">The Sagrada Familia is expected to be structurally completed by 2026, which marks the centennial of the architect Antoni Gaud√≠'s death. üèõÔ∏è This date has been confirmed by the organization responsible for managing the site. However, some additional decorative elements, such as sculptures and a controversial stairway, may not be finished until 2034. So, if you want to see the basilica in its complete glory, plan your trip for 2034 or later!</turn>
